-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Mon Dec 08, 2014 06:00AM EST
-- None



Dec 8 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1100 GMT on Monday:

** Three companies have emerged to make a joint bid for Citigroup Inc's <C.N> credit card business in Japan, the Nikkei reported, as the U.S. lender goes ahead with plans to exit consumer banking in the country. Shinsei Bank Ltd <8303.T>, department store operator Isetan Mitsukoshi Holdings Ltd <3099.T> and credit card service provider JCB Co Ltd want to buy the unit, which offers Diners Club credit cards in Japan, the business daily reported. [ID:nL3N0TP4KS]  ** Merck & Co Inc <MRK.N> is in talks to acquire Cubist Pharmaceuticals Inc <CBST.O> for more than $7 billion in a deal that could be announced as early as next week, the New York Times reported on Friday, citing people briefed on the matter. [ID:nL2N0TQ02D]  ** Songbird Estates Plc <SBDE.L> shareholder Madison International Realty plans to accept Qatar Investment Authority's offer for the British property company, said the sovereign wealth fund behind the hostile bid. [ID:nL6N0TS142]  ** France's Saint-Gobain <SGOB.PA> has offered 2.75 billion Swiss francs ($2.8 billion) to buy a controlling stake in chemicals group Sika AG <SIK.VX>, but the move was rejected by the Swiss firm's management. [ID:nL6N0TS0C8]  ** Some of the founders of Infosys Ltd <INFY.NS> want to sell shares in the Indian IT outsourcing company for $1.1 billion, a person familiar with the matter said, months after the company picked its first outsider as chief executive. [ID:nL3N0TS17F]  ** Royal Bank of Scotland Plc <RBS.L> has launched the sale of private bank Coutts International and has invited at least 10 potential suitors, including Credit Suisse Group AG <CSGN.VX>, Julius Baer Gruppe AG <BAER.VX> and Malayan Banking Bhd <MBBM.KL> to participate in an auction, sources said. [ID:nL3N0TP29L]  ** German publisher Axel Springer Se <SPRGn.DE> is spending 446 million euros ($548 million) in cash to lift its stake in a digital classified advertising joint venture to 85 from 70 percent as part of its efforts to shift from print to digital media. [ID:nL6N0TS0V6]  ** Saudi Arabia's National Industrialization Co <2060.SE> (Tasnee) has completed a 1.8 billion riyal ($480 million) deal to raise its majority stake in its Cristal subsidiary by a further 13 percentage points, it said in a statement on Sunday. [ID:nL6N0TR03U]  ** InterContinental Hotels Group <IHG.L>, one of the world's largest hoteliers, said it had agreed to sell its Paris-Le Grand hotel for 330 million euros ($405 million) to Constellation Hotels. [ID:nASN0005SY]  ** UK activist investment fund Crystal Amber Fund Ltd <CRSL.L> is in talks with several overseas investors about buying shares in J Sainsbury Plc's <SBRY.L>, as part of a plan to shake up the food retailer that could cause a takeover bid to be made, the Sunday Telegraph newspaper said. [ID:nL6N0TR0HF]  ** Japan's Sharp Corp <6753.T> said it was considering selling its U.S.-based solar energy development unit Recurrent Energy to Canadian Solar Inc <CSIQ.O>, but had yet to make a final decision on any deal. The Nikkei business daily reported on Sunday that Sharp had agreed to sell Recurrent to the Canadian firm for about 30 billion yen ($247 million). [ID:nL3N0TR01L]  ** Korea Electric Power Corp (KEPCO) <015760.KS> launched on Monday a selldown worth about $190 million in telecom company LG Uplus Corp <032640.KS>, according to a term sheet of the deal seen by Reuters. [ID:nL3N0TS2KM]  ** Motor insurer Esure Group Plc <ESUR.L> said it had conditionally agreed to buy the remaining 50 percent of Gocompare.com Holdings Ltd for 95 million pounds ($147.8 million), raising its holding in the price comparison website to 100 percent. [ID:nL3N0TS2JU]  ** South African fast-food chain firm Famous Brands Ltd <FBRJ.J> has bought a 75 percent stake in a local meat processing plant, it said, bulking up its supply chain to fight overseas competition. [ID:nL6N0TS1HZ]  ** Singapore state investor Temasek Holdings Ltd [TEM.UL] has agreed to buy a minority stake in Virtu Financial Inc [IPO-VIRT.O], the New York-based electronic dealing firm said, in a bet on the growth of automated trading globally. [ID:nL3N0TS1GA]